114	// the false->true transition and NOT on steady-state true polls. The steady-state assertion
115	// is the mutation discriminator — an implementation that returned true on every established
116	// poll (e.g. `return established`) would log the 'session established' record repeatedly and
117	// fail here, so this test kills that mutant.
